To Corky:<br>
     I've seen 84 Charlie Mopic and I consider it one of the best Vietnam films along with Hamburger Hill and Go Tell the Spartans.  84 Chalie is the story of a motion picture cameraman who goes along with a recon unit in Vietnam to create a training film.  The entire film is viewed through the camera of the cameraman, the viewer doesn't see the cameraman who is called Mopic (for motion picture) until the end.  It's a excellent movie that tries to capture the friendship and bond among the recon team members.  It was written and directed by a Nam vet, I believe the man who created Mr. Holland's Opus.  As a educator, I know many fellow educators that have shown 84 Charlie Mopic.  Check it out if you get the chance.  The formal title is 84 Charlie Mopic.  The movie was shown to the local Vietnam Veterans Group I work with and the guys enjoyed it very much and pointed out its accuracy in many details.  The movie focuses on just one recon unit in Nam, so if your looking for a movie on the big battles, this is not one. Take a look at it, I think you'll enjoy it.
